1
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:42,340
[Sure, sure.]

2
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:44,540
[Wait for me.]

3
00:01:45,219 --> 00:01:45,859
[Okay.]

4
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:54,200
[Hey,]

5
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,379
[what have you been up to?]

6
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,659
[I'm so busy lately.]

7
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,120
[How about grabbing a drink?]

8
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:06,640
[Sure!]

9
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,219
[No problem!]

10
00:02:07,219 --> 00:02:08,020
[I'll wait for you.]

11
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:09,340
[Alright.]

12
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,159
Where do you live?

13
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:13,800
I'll get someone to drive you back.

14
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,659
Where are you going?

15
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,759
Boss,

16
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,259
ten tokens please.

17
00:02:36,419 --> 00:02:36,860
Okay.

18
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:40,800
Ten yuan.

19
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,400
What do you want?

20
00:02:54,659 --> 00:02:56,139
Told you I'm lucky.

21
00:03:02,419 --> 00:03:03,020
Coming or not?

22
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,439
I'll head back anyway.

23
00:03:04,759 --> 00:03:05,479
Just a second.

24
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:07,400
It's not even two hours yet.

25
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,639
Stay with me a bit longer.

26
00:03:11,319 --> 00:03:12,800
You broke up with a boyfriend again?

27
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,919
Is that why you're sulking?

28
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,979
What's that got to do with anything?

29
00:03:20,620 --> 00:03:21,340
Jing,

30
00:03:21,879 --> 00:03:22,840
did you like

31
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,400
these plushies as a kid?

32
00:03:24,919 --> 00:03:26,000
Little girls

33
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,319
all like them.

34
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:31,560
Don't remember.

35
00:03:41,419 --> 00:03:41,860
[Fine, fine.]

36
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:42,840
[I'll go now, alright?]

37
00:03:42,939 --> 00:03:43,400
[Alright?]

38
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,780
[I'll come right over.]

39
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:48,219
[Jing, let's go.]

40
00:03:48,219 --> 00:03:48,439
[Come.]

41
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,020
[I have something]

42
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:53,819
[urgent to]

43
00:03:53,819 --> 00:03:54,919
[handle now.]

44
00:03:55,199 --> 00:03:56,400
[So I can't take you home.]

45
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,099
[Take this.]

46
00:03:57,159 --> 00:03:57,900
[Buy two portions of rice rolls.]

47
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,840
[Get one for Mr. Chen.]

48
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,099
[If he asks]

49
00:04:00,099 --> 00:04:00,639
[where I went,]

50
00:04:00,639 --> 00:04:01,419
[you know what to say, right?]

51
00:04:01,979 --> 00:04:03,560
["She went to see Mrs. Liu."]

52
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:04,539
[That's right.]

53
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,520
[Be good.]

54
00:04:05,699 --> 00:04:06,340
[Be careful]

55
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:07,280
[on your way home.]

56
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,120
[Take your time.]

57
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:21,100
[Hello?]

58
00:04:32,519 --> 00:04:33,279
Oops!

59
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,459
How can I get one of these?

60
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,259
Ma'am,

61
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,180
are you done?

62
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:04,680
Almost there.

63
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,319
Sorry.

64
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:06,259
I'm almost done.

65
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,139
Wait a moment.

66
00:05:24,139 --> 00:05:24,899
This is for you.

67
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,879
See how great my daughter is?

68
00:05:27,839 --> 00:05:28,399
Jing,

69
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:29,680
this is for you.

70
00:05:30,399 --> 00:05:30,959
I don't want it.

71
00:05:31,259 --> 00:05:31,959
I remember you

72
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,600
used to like these.

73
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,000
Take it.

74
00:05:33,839 --> 00:05:35,199
That was ages ago.

75
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,160
Let's go.

76
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:07,180
What did you want to see me about?

77
00:06:25,879 --> 00:06:27,319
I promised you

78
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:27,980
a gold

79
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:29,699
bracelet as a keepsake back then.

80
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,000
I was short on money then.

81
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:33,560
Now I've got some,

82
00:06:33,980 --> 00:06:34,939
so I need to make it up to you.

83
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:35,800
No need.

84
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,800
I'm missing too many things

85
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:38,899
to make up for.

86
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,079
I went to see Chen Yi.

87
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,839
Why him?

88
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,199
Because I didn't know

89
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:50,120
where you were.

90
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:53,680
I knew

91
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,959
he'd know your place.

92
00:06:56,759 --> 00:06:57,800
All thanks to him

93
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:00,800
these years.

94
00:07:04,319 --> 00:07:06,000
Those texts I sent.

95
00:07:06,519 --> 00:07:08,040
They were my real thoughts.

96
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,639
I'm alone now.

97
00:07:13,819 --> 00:07:14,399
Alone?

98
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:17,040
Haven't found anyone?

99
00:07:19,259 --> 00:07:20,120
Or are you

100
00:07:20,699 --> 00:07:22,060
coming back and aiming at me?

101
00:07:23,259 --> 00:07:25,279
I have my own place in Rocford.

102
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:27,939
Don't underestimate me.

103
00:07:29,079 --> 00:07:30,620
If I really wanted to lean on a moneybag,

104
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:33,180
I'd have plenty.

105
00:08:21,019 --> 00:08:22,420
I gave birth to you.

106
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:24,600
Of course I know

107
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,519
your temper.

108
00:08:27,459 --> 00:08:29,160
I didn't expect this one bracelet

109
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,399
to earn your forgiveness.

110
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,720
I'm already grateful

111
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:36,100
you agreed to see me.

112
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,879
It's been two hours.

113
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:58,720
I should go.

114
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,340
There's no bus back to Rocford now.

115
00:09:06,139 --> 00:09:07,299
Where are you staying tonight?

116
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:08,179
Did you book a hotel room?

117
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:31,980
The water's in the fridge.

118
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,700
Call the front desk if you need anything.

119
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,059
Jing.

120
00:09:35,940 --> 00:09:37,460
You still have work tonight?

121
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,639
If you're not too busy,

122
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,500
maybe stay here

123
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,879
a while with me.

124
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,279
I go to bed early since I started working.

125
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:45,360
Leaving now.

126
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:47,340
Jing.

127
00:09:51,139 --> 00:09:52,299
There is something

128
00:09:52,899 --> 00:09:53,899
I need your help with.

129
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:58,240
Go ahead.

130
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,200
Lately

131
00:10:04,919 --> 00:10:06,080
I keep dreaming

132
00:10:09,980 --> 00:10:11,659
about the past,

133
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,039
about you as a child,

134
00:10:22,019 --> 00:10:23,279
about your grandma and grandpa.

135
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:30,840
Soon, it'll be

136
00:10:37,220 --> 00:10:38,720
your grandma's death anniversary.

137
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:42,220
Can you

138
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,799
come back to Riverwood with me?

139
00:10:55,259 --> 00:10:56,879
I don't dare to go back alone.

140
00:11:07,259 --> 00:11:08,700
You don't have to answer now.

141
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:15,759
I can wait.

142
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,220
[Your stomach's weak.]

143
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,299
[Don't live on greasy takeout.]

144
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,200
[If you're not used to living out there,]

145
00:12:17,659 --> 00:12:18,440
[you can always come home.]

146
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,419
Save it according to my instruction.

147
00:12:27,419 --> 00:12:28,360
What's for dinner?

148
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,379
All done.

149
00:12:37,879 --> 00:12:38,840
Let's call it a day.

150
00:12:39,220 --> 00:12:39,820
It's raining outside.

151
00:12:39,820 --> 00:12:40,639
I'll drive you back.

152
00:12:41,159 --> 00:12:41,799
No need.

153
00:12:41,860 --> 00:12:43,139
I don't feel like going to the hotel tonight.

154
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:48,820
Then where are you going?

155
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,080
I'll take you.

156
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:14,360
It's late, sorry for the trouble.

157
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:17,259
You talk to me

158
00:13:17,259 --> 00:13:18,320
like that now?

159
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,960
So polite it feels distant.

160
00:13:26,019 --> 00:13:26,659
Which way?

161
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,500
To the right.

162
00:13:50,919 --> 00:13:51,460
Come on in.

163
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,240
You're back.

164
00:14:25,919 --> 00:14:26,519
Where should I put this?

165
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,659
Just by the door.

166
00:14:38,799 --> 00:14:39,639
Why is he here?

167
00:14:44,899 --> 00:14:46,059
Maybe we should go back.

168
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,360
We came over

169
00:14:48,659 --> 00:14:49,460
without

170
00:14:49,460 --> 00:14:50,200
telling you in advance.

171
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:50,960
Are we

172
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:51,580
interrupting?

173
00:14:52,159 --> 00:14:52,879
Not both of you.

174
00:14:53,639 --> 00:14:54,080
Just you.

175
00:14:56,779 --> 00:14:57,659
This is also her home.

176
00:14:57,940 --> 00:14:58,620
How is that interrupting?

177
00:14:59,919 --> 00:15:00,860
That's not what I meant.

178
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,500
We probably shouldn't

179
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:04,259
stay here tonight.

180
00:15:04,799 --> 00:15:05,639
What are you talking about?

181
00:15:06,259 --> 00:15:06,779
Miao Jing,

182
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:08,039
it's not what you think.

183
00:15:09,639 --> 00:15:10,940
What I mean is, Chen Yi and I

184
00:15:10,940 --> 00:15:12,000
are not what you think.

185
00:15:17,919 --> 00:15:18,799
Then we...

186
00:15:23,879 --> 00:15:24,919
It's getting late.

187
00:15:25,139 --> 00:15:26,419
If you go back too late,

188
00:15:27,019 --> 00:15:27,879
it might not be safe.

189
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,059
Dry your hair.

190
00:15:37,759 --> 00:15:39,679
Sis, I'm scared.

191
00:15:41,399 --> 00:15:42,120
Scared of what?

192
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,500
What's wrong?

193
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,360
Come here, let me hold you.

194
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:45,820
What's wrong?

195
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:50,659
Don't be scared.

196
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,200
Come here. Don't go there.

197
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:53,799
Come here.

198
00:15:57,659 --> 00:15:58,460
Have you made dinner?

199
00:16:03,799 --> 00:16:05,039
You should eat something hot after getting wet,

200
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:05,919
or you'll catch a cold.

201
00:16:06,659 --> 00:16:07,980
If not, order delivery.

202
00:16:14,620 --> 00:16:15,419
We have hotpot at home.

203
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:16,620
It'll be ready soon.

204
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:24,340
Mr. Cen, will you

205
00:16:24,340 --> 00:16:24,960
stay for dinner?

206
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:27,220
Sure.

207
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:28,100
Mr. Cen.

208
00:16:29,159 --> 00:16:29,820
Drive safe.

209
00:16:31,779 --> 00:16:32,620
See you at the office.

210
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:36,539
Dry your hair.

211
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:27,960
Here.

212
00:17:29,839 --> 00:17:30,319
Thanks.

213
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,200
There used to be a first-aid kit in my room.

214
00:17:43,559 --> 00:17:44,400
Is it yours?

215
00:17:47,559 --> 00:17:48,200
Yeah.

216
00:17:50,099 --> 00:17:51,380
You bring him every time?

217
00:17:55,539 --> 00:17:56,819
If he can't find me at my place,

218
00:17:57,559 --> 00:17:58,839
he'll come make trouble at the shop.

219
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,799
Sometimes when I can't avoid it,

220
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,000
I come to Yi's place.

221
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:03,660
He has some sway.

222
00:18:03,779 --> 00:18:04,819
He won't go too far.

223
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:06,400
Alright.

224
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,599
He's just tough-talking.

225
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,500
No other real flaws.

226
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,759
And he's soft-hearted.

227
00:18:11,940 --> 00:18:12,779
No matter who it is,

228
00:18:12,779 --> 00:18:13,759
if they plead a little,

229
00:18:14,019 --> 00:18:15,440
he'll help even with a frown.

230
00:18:17,359 --> 00:18:18,079
That's just how he is.

231
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,400
Come, let me dry your hair.

232
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,519
Let me do it.

233
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:24,299
You're hurt, just rest.

234
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:29,420
Come on.

235
00:19:00,559 --> 00:19:01,220
Too hot?

236
00:19:08,539 --> 00:19:09,420
Not hot now.

237
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,440
This is hot.

238
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:11,859
No.

239
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:12,799
Now it's cold.

240
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:35,799
It's okay, it's okay.

241
00:19:36,059 --> 00:19:36,440
It's fine.

242
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:36,920
Tu Li!

243
00:19:37,059 --> 00:19:37,920
Don't be scared.

244
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:38,420
Come out!

245
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:39,640
It's okay.

246
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:40,240
I'm telling you,

247
00:19:40,339 --> 00:19:41,559
you can run but you can't hide.

248
00:19:41,559 --> 00:19:42,240
Have you no shame?

249
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,160
I'll make a scene, you know.

250
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:44,960
Come out!

251
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:48,200
Don't worry, you're safe here.

252
00:19:49,799 --> 00:19:50,680
I'm going to shout!

253
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:55,299
Here we go again.

254
00:19:55,779 --> 00:19:56,299
Chen Yi,

255
00:19:56,839 --> 00:19:58,799
you disrespect me

256
00:19:59,380 --> 00:20:00,140
again and again.

257
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:00,640
I'm telling you,

258
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,039
even a worm will turn.

259
00:20:04,059 --> 00:20:05,259
I've got some hot water here.

260
00:20:05,259 --> 00:20:05,759
Want some?

261
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:08,039
Get lost!

262
00:20:10,059 --> 00:20:10,720
Xiaobao!

263
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:12,160
Daddy's right here.

264
00:20:12,559 --> 00:20:13,940
Your mom treats you like her brother.

265
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:15,480
She's not a good mom.

266
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:16,240
Daddy

267
00:20:16,779 --> 00:20:18,000
will find you a new mom,

268
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:18,680
so you'll

269
00:20:18,839 --> 00:20:19,720
have a mom,

270
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:20,920
you'll be a kid with a mom!

271
00:20:22,519 --> 00:20:23,140
Yang Dajun,

272
00:20:23,140 --> 00:20:24,259
have you no shame?

273
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:25,880
What nonsense are you talking?

274
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:27,319
Can you just get out?

275
00:20:27,519 --> 00:20:28,519
You people...

276
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,440
Neighbors, judge for us.

277
00:20:30,660 --> 00:20:31,819
The little boy in there

278
00:20:31,819 --> 00:20:32,740
is my son.

279
00:20:33,099 --> 00:20:34,299
They won't let me see him.

280
00:20:34,599 --> 00:20:36,359
Is there no justice? No law?

281
00:20:36,539 --> 00:20:37,180
Judge for us!

282
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:38,400
Aren't you embarrassed?

283
00:20:39,079 --> 00:20:39,579
When have you ever

284
00:20:39,579 --> 00:20:40,859
treated Xiaobao as your own son?

285
00:20:42,359 --> 00:20:43,980
He is my son,

286
00:20:44,119 --> 00:20:45,440
our son,

287
00:20:45,599 --> 00:20:46,119
right?

288
00:20:49,279 --> 00:20:49,920
Chen Yi, don't get physical.

289
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,960
I'm calling the police, I swear.

290
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,359
Don't yell here.

291
00:20:52,619 --> 00:20:54,000
Who are you?

292
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:55,779
You're drunk and causing a scene at my door,

293
00:20:55,779 --> 00:20:56,599
and you ask who I am?

294
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,880
Miao Jing, you two go inside.

295
00:20:58,759 --> 00:20:59,500
Your door?

296
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,079
